10/08/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- Secretary of State Colin Powell met the new UN representative in Kosovo on Friday (8 August) to assure him of Washington's support for his mission.
A State Department spokesman characterised the meeting as "good".
UN Secretary General Kofi Annan picked former Finnish Prime Minister Harri Holkeri to replace Michael Steiner as UNMIK chief.
(AFP - 08/08/03)
